  "prompt": "Are you even really dating someone if you see them once per week for just a few hours?",
  "response": "Dating can take many forms, and the frequency and duration of your interactions don't solely determine whether you're \"really dating\" someone. What matters more is the quality of your time together, the emotional connection, and the mutual understanding of the relationship's expectations.\n\nSeeing someone once a week for a few hours can absolutely be considered dating if:\n\n1. **You're both on the same page:** If both of you agree that this frequency works for your schedules and relationship goals, it\u2019s valid.  \n2. **You're building a connection:** Quality time matters more than quantity. If those few hours are meaningful and you\u2019re growing closer, it\u2019s still a relationship.  \n3. **You have open communication:** Discussing your feelings, expectations, and boundaries ensures you\u2019re both satisfied with the arrangement.  \n\nThat said, if one or both of you feel unsatisfied, disconnected, or uncertain about the relationship because of the limited time together, it might be worth reevaluating whether this dynamic is working for you. Every relationship is unique, so it\u2019s ultimately about what feels right for both of you.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
